#7543
Stained-Glass Hallway~
~
Both walls of this long hallway are lined with vivid stained-glass windows.  
Scenes of sunsets, clouds, and starry skies give the area a very somber 
feeling.  Some of the fifty windows depict the tell-tale funnel of a tornado 
descending from the base of a massive cloud.  A great many more of the 
glassworks have been constructed into the presentation of a voluminous tome. 
 A large dias stands at the far east end of this fused-silica passage.  
~
